<L>__{103. mizzen topgallant day}
<A>__{mowett stands in the cross trees, making a final check on the lashings round the new mizzen top. below him the great work is nearing completion, men swarming like ants over every part of the hull. mowett climbs down past faster doudle who has one leg looped through the shrouds and is splicing a rope with both hands and his teeth. farther down, a patched sail is being furled up tight in its gaskets. beyond that, at the base of the main mast a fascinated group of men have gathered to watch the doctor trepanning joe}
<B>__{plaice.}
